  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL · 📋 REASON: code-impl in BFF (.cs file modification, tag bff-api, LLM call + error mapping is semantically load-bearing, ADR-013+038 applicable) — quality gates Step 9.5 required · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Load context">
      Read project CLAUDE.md + spec.md FR-12 + .claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md + task 001 pattern-decision doc + task 003 modified executor file.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Re-read AiAnalysisNodeExecutor LLM-call section">
      Identify exactly: (a) the IOpenAiClient.GetStructuredCompletionRawAsync invocation signature + parameter order, (b) telemetry tags emitted around the call, (c) how the response is parsed to JsonElement, (d) how errors are mapped to NodeOutput.Error + NodeErrorCodes.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Implement the LLM call">
      Edit AiCompletionNodeExecutor.cs ExecuteAsync(): replace the task-003 TODO with:
      - var response = await _openAiClient.GetStructuredCompletionRawAsync(mergedSystemPrompt, mergedOutputSchema, mergedTemperature, cancellationToken)
      - Parse response to JsonElement (mirror AiAnalysisNodeExecutor parsing path)
      - Emit telemetry tags: node.id, action_type=AiCompletion, llm.deployment, llm.tokens (if available)
      - Bind JsonElement to NodeOutput.Ok with node.Id + node.OutputVariable + metrics
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement error mapping">
      Wrap the LLM call in try/catch:
      - JsonException (malformed response) → NodeOutput.Error(NodeErrorCodes.InvalidResponse, "LLM returned malformed JSON: {msg}")
      - HttpRequestException / OperationCanceledException (LLM HTTP error) → NodeOutput.Error(NodeErrorCodes.LlmCallFailed or matching code, "LLM call failed: {msg}")
      - General Exception → NodeOutput.Error(NodeErrorCodes.InternalError, ex.Message)
      Mirror AiAnalysisNodeExecutor's error mapping if more specific codes exist there.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Confirm cancellation propagation">
      Verify CancellationToken is passed to IOpenAiClient.GetStructuredCompletionRawAsync (no silent drop).
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Build">
      Run: dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ — expect 0 errors, 0 new warnings.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify existing tests still pass">
      Run: dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ — expect no regression.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Publish + size check (partial)">
      Run: dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish-task004/ — measure compressed size delta vs task 003 baseline. Document.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify acceptance">
      Re-read AiCompletionNodeExecutor.cs; confirm all goal bullets satisfied; the executor's happy path is now complete end-to-end (modulo Validate() task 005).
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `/code-review` on the modified file. Run `/adr-check` against ADR-010 + ADR-013 + ADR-029 + ADR-038 + bff-extensions.md. Fix findings before commit.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Update current-task.md + TASK-INDEX">
      Mark task 004 status complete; advance current-task.md.
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Commit">
      Commit AiCompletionNodeExecutor.cs change with conventional message.
      Example: feat(bff/r7): IOpenAiClient call + JsonElement output binding in AiCompletionNodeExecutor (Wave 1 task 004, FR-12)
    </step>
  </steps>

